Summary: Unidentifiable picture on digital camenra over the ocean. Not visualized with naked eye.
divs: Sighting DetailsI took a picture on the coast of South Carolina last weekend. I was with a friend at the beach. I was attempting to take a picture with a Canon EOS digital camera in the pitch blackness and catch the tide coming in in the darkness. I took a series of pictures, but in one of the pictures, this showed up. I would like to know if this is an issue with my camera, reflection or any other phenomenon or if this could possibly more than that. I am not a professional photographer or UFO expert. I took the picture in the presence of a crecent moon, to the far right of me but not anywhere near the photo direction. I didn't visualize anything on the horizon or anywhere else in the enviroment that could have persuaded the picture in this way. This showed in the picture. I don't have adequate software to zoom in and not lose resolution but I have attached also the zoom that I can do on my computer. It looks like water coming off of the object once zoomed. Maybe this in nothing at all, but I'm very curious. Does anyone have any ideas?
